Subject: Re: [T2] Spark Plugs Bosch vs NGK

On Mon, 12 May 2003, Faster-Laster wrote:

> Hopefully I won't add fuel to the fire, but... Doktor Tim has many
> times commented to use the proper Bosch plugs in VWs. Terry recently
> mentioned using NGK Platnium. What I find interesting is that in my
> new longblock from Mexico it came with NGK plugs in it. Not platnium,
> just regular ones. Anyone care to comment on vw's apparent switch to
> NGK. At least south of the border.

Mine came with them too.  I have a lot of experience with NGK plugs and
they are very consistent in quality.  The threads are always cut very
well, which is of prime concern with aluminum heads.  I don't have any
problem recommending NGK plugs of the proper heat range in VW engines.

George Lyle
